      "title": "IMF chief pleased over SL reaching staff-level pact for US $ 2.9bn",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "International Monetary Fund chief Kristalina Georgieva said today that she is very pleased that IMF staff and Sri Lankan government officials have reached a staff-level agreement to support the country\u2019s economic policies with a 48-month Extended Fund Facility of about US$2.9 billion.",
        "The IMF on Thursday announced that it has reached a staff-level agreement with Sri Lanka, in a first step before extending a $2.9 billion loan package that the Fund has made contingent on assurances from the island nation\u2019s creditors.(DSB)"
      ],
